# Phase 4: Verification

Execute comprehensive verification of all generated content.

## Objective

Verify all output content meets quality standards, maintains source fidelity, and is appropriate for {{ target_audience }}.

## Prerequisites

Phase 3 completed with all content generated.

## Tasks

### Content Fidelity Verification
- Verify all claims traceable to sources
- Check for any external information
- Validate reasoning documentation alignment

### Data Verification
- Extract all statistics and data points
- Verify against source materials
- Confirm accuracy of any transformations

### Consistency Verification
- Check terminology consistency across outputs
- Verify no contradictions between sections
- Validate cross-references

### Audience Appropriateness
- Review language for target audience
- Verify relevance of content
- Check for actionable insights

### Prohibited Content Scan
- Search for content outside source materials
- Verify no post-source information
- Confirm compliance with project constraints

## Outputs

- Verification reports for each output
- `/2-work-in-progress/VERIFICATION-RESULTS.md` - Overall summary
- Issue log with recommendations (if any)

## Completion Criteria

- [ ] All content verified against sources
- [ ] Statistics and data validated
- [ ] Consistency verified across outputs
- [ ] Audience appropriateness confirmed
- [ ] No prohibited content found
- [ ] Verification reports complete
